sec.p:
The rules of the Regulatory Agencies we studied (regarding the production of API/SI) can be divided into three types: 
   
    

CM is permitted only where adequate technical/organisational measures are used as well as adequate cleaning measures that can guarantee the safety of the method: Health Canada, EMA, PIC/S, FDA;
    
    

CM is permitted for the production of certain classes of API/SI only in exceptional circumstances: CFDA, WHO, ANVISA. CFDA and WHO allow CM only for the production of “certain” API and in exceptional circumstances (without defining in the regulations which circumstances can be defined as exceptional). ANVISA allows the use of CM only in the case of serious emergencies (i.e.: war, fires, floods);
    
    

CM is not provided or mentioned: COFEPRIS, CDSCO.
